03/03/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The foreign ministry issued a press release Saturday (1 March), welcoming the US decision to grant Romania the status of a functioning market economy as of 10 March.
US Commerce Secretary Donald Evans confirmed the plan during a visit Friday to Bucharest, aimed at boosting trade relations between the two countries.
The status upgrade will provide more favourable terms for export to the US market.
(Mediafax, Rompres - 03/03/03)
